<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Mohamed Salah paid tribute to his seriously ill Egypt team-mate Moamen Zakaria after scoring a hat-trick in Liverpool's 4-3 victory over Leeds.</p>

<p>The forward celebrated his third goal at Anfield - his second from the penalty spot - by emulating Zakaria's celebration, pressing his hands over his ears.</p>

<p>Zakaria is suffering with incurable Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS), commonly know as Motor Neuron Disease, which affects the brain and spinal chord. </p>

<p>Mohamed Salah paid tribute to Moamen Zakaria after scoring his hat-trick goal against Leeds</p>
